content.description: Sit start on the far left side of the arete, and move up and over at the apex of the boulder. The holds are good, but the landing is questionable near the start. Once you're at the apex, there is another boulder 12 inches below. So while the fall is not bad, it is not all that able to have a spotter.
content.protection: A pad and a spotter (if you can figure out where to spot from).
content.location: This is located on the north face of the boulder, starting on the left side and moving up and right. There are several options to downclimb off the top.

content.description:
This is a variation of

You 666ed It

with a start that requires a bit more power. Sit start utilizing the crimp rail in the middle of the north face with slim feet. Move up to the arete, and top out at the apex of the north face.
content.location: This is located in the center of the north face of the boulder. The downclimb options are numerous on the south and east sides.
